column2: Use of a cryptographic key that is too small may allow the encryption to be broken.
column4: Creation of an RSA key uses [["1048"|"relative:///CWE-326/author_1.py:9:18:9:21"]] bits, which is below 2048 and considered breakable.

column2: Use of a cryptographic key that is too small may allow the encryption to be broken.
column4: Creation of an DSA key uses [["1024"|"relative:///CWE-326/author_2.py:7:25:7:28"]] bits, which is below 2048 and considered breakable.
